t\\n    void diagnosticsProbeResourcesWhileRejectingNonLogAdapter() {\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    @Order(1)\\n    void diagnosticsProbeResourcesWhileRejectingNonLogAdapter() {\"}]}\n8105:  8105\t[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating class loader behavior**\\n\\nI’m trying to understand how the `getLowest` function works in relation to platform and app. It seems that `getLowest(platform, app)` returns the app, right? So, if I check if the platform is an ancestor in `cl1`, it traverses the parents for `cl2`, but it doesn’t match. However, when it goes from `cl2` to `cl1`, it finds the platform and returns `cl2` (thisClassLoader) instead of the context. That’s interesting!\\n\\n**Considering test setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the constructor sets the String and LogFactory fields, along with possibly class$. If the first test runs, class$ might get covered, but it seems it didn't. The String test runs class$ Log, so I'm wondering if I should add a TestMethodOrder to make `diagnosticsProbeResources...` first. This would ensure class$ Log gets covered before any other sets, but I’m unsure if order is actually pertinent. Maybe using alphabetical order for the methods could work?\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_096547c64b0e67700169f93fc852ac819dad1becc1cc7a2cd1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-T_nSDCEqjahQexNomUZ066opikMeUr-R1Q2oVAMzZfU4EwJflxf9xp8Z7IBTq19hgb9jX8MQDHUK-ufZPTHn76ES4oTv0eoO0VhLOzXVrhU4WkqOd7fNnd7rOT259P51mvwNM37bXhqj8mO9zOYJgB0bW06JPPvxdC0WyNnyfJIr_jU8xat82MwmT2djUf3LS8zah-2iVQS471HhL3-xJnPD-HE14EMLmZo4Vg6n3o7T5SyMPczpifjobOV3z-_hk6K5P0MrM92Lx7vgeP0oqAnE5VfgzTbJApam_2UsHD8evedXh7ngePiEtt8VA4dgT7QNITh-g2K7IWf8TTwQTVn2JEB6vHslMjCCK7ZeHCCPSEUuHaGw-Gc17phoZpErBDUni-84gK39LhD4kfSJ_o5mUmGNCdScZ-qAQq0p8NMPEkLhrUnoz1WtoqiBoT0diu_lpfDkFdYAjWk1uG-GLgbZhevhxQPuQclXm5meRr-rs2EVlv8C5wsjTWw9nvbsyGScWVjF0