{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_53","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2889-library-new-request-org.apache.htrace-htrace-core-3.1.0-incubating-1d1b79d3\n\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / coverage improvement for the new-library request. The failed `dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.5` run ended with `status=failure` after 3 iterations, but still reported `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and no recorded test or metadata artifacts in `stats/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/execution-metrics.json`. The preserved test project also still contains the untouched scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/src/test/java/org_apache_htrace/htrace_core/Htrace_coreTest.java`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` reason.\n\nCoverage is also far below the new-library bar: `tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports only 20/103 covered calls (19.42%). Large areas are still uncovered, including `org.apache.htrace.commons.logging.LogSource`, `org.apache.htrace.SamplerBuilder`, `org.apache.htrace.SpanReceiverBuilder`, and much of the relocated Jackson surface. The preserved branch does contain a partial follow-up (`CommonsLoggingTest` plus metadata), but it is not enough to clear the coverage gate.\n\nThere is also a tooling problem when trying to continue with metadata generation: `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T00-44-28-904950Z.log` and `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-05T00-45-53-998010Z.log` fail while instrumenting tests with the GraalVM native-image agent (`Could not find agent library native-image-agent...`). A later follow-up in `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows the same flow still failing during `generateMetadata`, this time with a native-image-agent JVM startup/guarantee failure.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T00-44-28-845646Z.log`\n- `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T00-44-28-904950Z.log`\n- `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-05T00-45-53-998010Z.log`\n- `logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Replace the scaffold `Htrace_coreTest` with real library-specific tests that exercise HTrace’s reflective/plugin paths beyond commons-logging, especially `LogSource`, `SamplerBuilder`, and `SpanReceiverBuilder`.\n2. Use the preserved branch as a starting point, but refresh the tests/metadata until dynamic-access coverage is above the 50% gate.\n3. Fix or standardize the GraalVM `native-image-agent` setup before rerunning `generateMetadata`, since current runs are blocked during agent startup."}}
